Yes. The Hollywood Reporter site provides a newsletter subscription option.

**Location(s) on the page**
1. **Footer – “Newsletter Sign Up”**  
   - Appears near the bottom of the page under the heading **“Newsletter Sign Up.”**  
   - Contains an email input field labeled “Your Email” and a **“Subscribe” / “Sign Up”** button.

2. **Footer – “Alerts & Newsletters”**  
   - Another section titled **“Alerts & Newsletters”** with the same email field and **“Subscribe / Sign Up”** button.

3. **Top navigation – “Newsletters” link**  
   - At the top of the page there is a **“Newsletters”** link that leads to a subscription area showing **“The Definitive Voice of Entertainment News – Subscribe for full access to The Hollywood Reporter – See My Options Sign Up.”**

**How to subscribe**
- Enter your email address in the provided “Your Email” field.  
- Click the **“Subscribe”** (or **“Sign Up”**) button.  
- The form confirms that you agree to the Terms of Use and Privacy Policy and processes the subscription (protected by reCAPTCHA).
</result>


